   <div id="news">
    <article class="post-3798 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news" id="post-3798">
     <div class="date">
      February 20, 2019
     </div>
     <h2 class="entry-title">
      <a href="https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/2019/02/next-fortcast-event-to-discuss-colorado-snow-survey/" rel="bookmark">
       Next FORTCAST event to discuss Colorado Snow Survey
      </a>
     </h2>
     <div class="featured-image">
      <a href="https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/2019/02/next-fortcast-event-to-discuss-colorado-snow-survey/">
       <img alt="Karl Wetlaufer" class="attachment-240x160 size-240x160 wp-post-image" height="160" sizes="(max-width: 228px) 100vw, 228px" src="https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.26.19_WhatsBrewing_Wetlaufer.jpg" srcset="https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.26.19_WhatsBrewing_Wetlaufer.jpg 750w, https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/2.26.19_WhatsBrewing_Wetlaufer-300x210.jpg 300w" width="228">
       </img>
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="entry-content">
      Brian Domonkos is supervisor of the Colorado Snow Survey, overseeing snow monitoring operations in Colorado, Arizona, New Mexico and southern Wyoming. Learn more about our precious Colorado snowpack at FORTCAST's next What's Brewing in Weather &amp; Climate talk. The discussion topic will be the Colorado Snow Survey, which provides mountain snowpack data and streamflow forecasts for the western United States. Its applications include water supply management, flood control, climate modeling,…
     </div>
    </article>
    <article class="post-3792 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-news" id="post-3792">
     <div class="date">
      February 18, 2019
     </div>
     <h2 class="entry-title">
      <a href="https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/2019/02/entomologists-will-talk-bugs-at-march-teen-science-cafe/" rel="bookmark">
       Entomologists will talk bugs at March Teen Science Café
      </a>
     </h2>
     <div class="featured-image">
      <a href="https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/2019/02/entomologists-will-talk-bugs-at-march-teen-science-cafe/">
       <img alt="Erika Peirce and Melissa Schreiner" class="attachment-240x160 size-240x160 wp-post-image" height="160" sizes="(max-width: 207px) 100vw, 207px" src="https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.13.19_TSC_PeirceandSchreiner.jpg" srcset="https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.13.19_TSC_PeirceandSchreiner.jpg 750w, https://www.atmos.colostate.edu/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/3.13.19_TSC_PeirceandSchreiner-300x232.jpg 300w" width="207">
       </img>
      </a>
     </div>
     <div class="entry-content">
      What's it like working in the world of arthropods and Colorado insects? Bring your entomology questions to March's Teen Science Café. CSU entomology graduate students Erika Peirce and Melissa Schreiner will answer questions about insects, jobs, college, social media, travel, beekeeping, macrophotography and insect collecting. When: 5-7 p.m., with the presentation starting at 5:30 p.m., Wednesday, March 13.Where: Everyday Joe’s Coffee House, 144 S. Mason St., Fort CollinsPresenters: CSU entomology…
